# Logical Operators: Python offers "or","and" and "not" as a logical operators 
# These operator are beneficial for conditional statements:
# AND : If both side, left and right, are True, then the AND operator returns True.
# Or : If any side is True, then the OR operator returns True.
# NOT : THE "not" operator inverts the outcome of the condition. If a condition in the not operator returns true, then the "not" operator makes it False, vice verse.
A = 11
print(A>=10 and A<=50)
B = 0.5
print(B>=10 and B<=50)
C = 51
print(C>=10 and C<=50)